Quota for use:¶

https://developers.google.com/youtube/v3/determine_quota_cost?hl=pt-br

https://support.google.com/youtube/thread/1382733?hl=en

https://developers.google.com/youtube/v3/getting-started#quota

  • Search (list, snippet) : 102
  • Video (list, statistics): 3
  • Video (list, statistics,snippet): 5
  • commentThread (list,snippet): 3*#Comment/100
  • channels (list, snippet,statistics): 5
In [8]:
def get_youtube_search_stats(youtube, search, desiredResults,createCSV=False,output_dir='',filename='video_result.csv'):

    response_list=[]
    video_dict={}
    video_list=[]
    pages=1
    videos=0
    
    if desiredResults > 50:
        max_results = 50
    else:
        max_results = desiredResults
    
    max_pages = math.ceil(desiredResults/max_results)
    
    match = youtube.search().list(q=search, part="snippet", maxResults=max_results).execute()
    try:
        next_page_token = match["nextPageToken"]
    except:
        print("No more pages")  
    response_list.append(match)
    
    while ('nextPageToken' in match and pages <= max_pages):
        print(pages)
        match = youtube.search().list(q=search, part="snippet", maxResults=max_results,pageToken=next_page_token).execute()
        response_list.append(match)
        try:
            next_page_token = match["nextPageToken"]
        except:
            print("No more pages")
        pages+=1
    
    for response in response_list:
        for search_result in response.get("items", []):
            if search_result["id"]["kind"] == "youtube#video":
                #videos.append("%s (%s)" % (search_result["snippet"]["title"],search_result["id"]["videoId"]))
                title = search_result["snippet"]["title"]
                title = unidecode.unidecode(title)
                videoId = search_result["id"]["videoId"]
                
                publishedAt = search_result["snippet"]['publishedAt']
                channelId = search_result["snippet"]['channelId']
                channelTitle = search_result["snippet"]['channelTitle']
                
                video_response = youtube.videos().list(id=videoId,part="snippet,statistics").execute()
                for video_result in video_response.get("items",[]):
                    #print(video_result)
                    if 'tags' in video_result['snippet']:
                        tags = video_result['snippet']['tags']
                    else:
                        tags=''
                    if 'description' in video_result['snippet']:
                        description = video_result['snippet']['description']
                    else:
                        description=''
                    if 'categoryId' in video_result['snippet']:                        
                        categoryId = video_result['snippet']['categoryId']
                    else:
                        categoryId = None
                    
                    viewCount = video_result["statistics"]["viewCount"]
                    if 'likeCount' not in video_result["statistics"]:
                        likeCount = 0
                    else:
                        likeCount = video_result["statistics"]["likeCount"]
                    if 'dislikeCount' not in video_result["statistics"]:
                        dislikeCount = 0
                    else:
                        dislikeCount = video_result["statistics"]["dislikeCount"]
                    if 'commentCount' not in video_result["statistics"]:
                        commentCount = 0
                    else:
                        commentCount = video_result["statistics"]["commentCount"]
                    if 'favoriteCount' not in video_result["statistics"]:
                        favoriteCount = 0
                    else:
                        favoriteCount = video_result["statistics"]["favoriteCount"]

                video_dict={'title':title,'videoId':videoId,'viewCount':int(viewCount),'likeCount':int(likeCount),
                                'dislikeCount':int(dislikeCount),'commentCount':int(commentCount),
                            'favoriteCount':int(favoriteCount),'description':description,'tags':tags,
                            'categoryId':categoryId,'channelId':channelId,
                            'channelTitle':channelTitle,'publishedAt':publishedAt}
                video_list.append(video_dict)
                
                if videos >= desiredResults:
                    break
                videos+=1
            
    video_dataframe = pd.DataFrame(video_list)
            
    if createCSV:
        video_dataframe.to_csv(output_dir+search+'_'+filename,sep=';')

    print("Quota cost for this requisition: " +str(videos*5+pages*102))
    return video_dataframe

Sum of views by channel (considering the 500 videos search)¶

Curiosamente, enquanto os outros bancos digitais aparecem com mais visualizações, o canal do Nubank não aparece nessa lista.

In [21]:
channelViews = df[['channelTitle','viewCount']].groupby('channelTitle').sum().sort_values('viewCount',ascending=False).head(50).reset_index()

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(16, 24))
#sns.set(style="default")

b = sns.barplot(x='viewCount',y='channelTitle',data=channelViews)
b.axes.set_title("Channel Views",fontsize=22)
ax.tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=22)

Create a List with all tags¶

In [22]:
tags_list=[]
for tags in list(df['tags']):
    for tag in tags:
        tags_list.append(tag.lower())
In [23]:
len(tags_list)
Out[23]:
7316

Plot most common tags¶

In [24]:
from collections import Counter
import numpy as np

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(16, 24))


#tagsCount = Counter(tags_list)
tagsCount = dict(Counter(tags_list).most_common(50))

#labels, values = zip(*tagsCount.items())

labels = list(tagsCount.values())
values = list(tagsCount.keys())

b = sns.barplot(x=labels,y=values)

b.axes.set_title("Most common tags",fontsize=22)
ax.tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=22)

Now let's take a look at Comments¶

In [26]:
def load_comments(match):
    comment_list=[]
    comment_dict={}
    for item in match["items"]:
        videoId = item['snippet']['videoId']
        commentThreadId = item['id']
        commentThreadEtag = item['etag']
        comment = item["snippet"]["topLevelComment"]
        commentId = comment['id']
        commentEtag = comment['etag']
        author = comment["snippet"]["authorDisplayName"]
        authorChannelId = comment["snippet"]['authorChannelId']['value']
        text = comment["snippet"]["textDisplay"]
        viewerRating = comment["snippet"]['viewerRating']
        likeCount = comment["snippet"]['likeCount']
        publishedAt = comment["snippet"]['publishedAt']
        totalReplyCount = item["snippet"]['totalReplyCount']
         
        comment_dict={'videoId':videoId,'commentThreadId':commentThreadId,'commentThreadEtag':commentThreadEtag,
                    'commentId':commentId,'commentEtag':commentEtag,'author':author,
                    'authorChannelId':authorChannelId,'text':text,'viewerRating':viewerRating,
                    'likeCount':int(likeCount),'totalReplyCount':int(totalReplyCount),
                    'publishedAt':publishedAt}
        #print(comment_dict)
        comment_list.append(comment_dict)
        #print(comment_list)
    return comment_list
    #return comment_list
        #print("Comment by {}: {}".format(author, text))
        #if 'replies' in item.keys():
        #if item['snippet']['totalReplyCount'] > 0:
            #for reply in item['replies']['comments']:
            #    rauthor = reply['snippet']['authorDisplayName']
            #    rtext = reply["snippet"]["textDisplay"]
            #replies_list.append(item['snippet']['totalReplyCount'])
        #    print("\n\tReply by {}: {}".format(rauthor, rtext), "\n")
   # return comment_list,replies_list

def get_comment_threads(youtube, video_id,pageToken=None):
    results = youtube.commentThreads().list(
        part="snippet",#,replies",
        maxResults=100,
        videoId=video_id,
        textFormat="plainText",
        pageToken=pageToken
    ).execute()
    return results

Run for all comments¶

In [27]:
def get_video_comments(youtube, videoId,createCSV=False,output_dir='',filename='video_comments.csv'):
    comments_list=[]
    
    match = get_comment_threads(youtube, videoId)
    try:
        next_page_token = match["nextPageToken"]
    except:
        print("Finished")    
    comments = load_comments(match)
    comments_list.extend(comments)
    #print("Replies",replies)
    pages=1
    while ('nextPageToken' in match):
        print(pages)
        #print(next_page_token)
        match = get_comment_threads(youtube, videoId,next_page_token)
        #comments_list.extend(load_comments(match))
        comments = load_comments(match)
        comments_list.extend(comments)
        #print("Replies",replies)
        try:
            next_page_token = match["nextPageToken"]
        except:
            print("Finished")
        pages+=1
            
    comments_dataframe = pd.DataFrame(comments_list)
            
    if createCSV:
        comments_dataframe.to_csv(output_dir+videoId+'_'+filename,sep=';')

    print("Quota cost for this requisition: " +str(pages*3))
    return comments_dataframe

from nltk.corpus import stopwords
from string import punctuation
stopwords = set(stopwords.words('portuguese') + list(punctuation))
otherstopwords = ['..','oi',' ...','...','....','pra']
palavras_sem_stopwords = [palavra for palavra in palavras if palavra not in stopwords]
palavras_sem_stopwords = [palavra for palavra in palavras_sem_stopwords if palavra not in otherstopwords]

In [41]:
###Create a score (simple one) to each sentence based on the most important words
from collections import defaultdict
sentencas_importantes = defaultdict(int)
for i, sentenca in enumerate(sentencas):
    for palavra in word_tokenize(sentenca.lower()):
        if palavra in frequencia:
            sentencas_importantes[i] += frequencia[palavra]
In [42]:
###Select Highest score sentences
from heapq import nlargest
idx_sentencas_importantes = nlargest(5, sentencas_importantes, sentencas_importantes.get)
In [43]:

###Analyze bigrams
from nltk.util import ngrams 

bigrams = []
for sentence in sentencas:
    sequence = word_tokenize(sentence)
    palavras_sem_stopwords = [palavra for palavra in sequence if palavra not in stopwords]
    palavras_sem_stopwords = [palavra.lower() for palavra in palavras_sem_stopwords if palavra not in otherstopwords]
    bigrams.extend(list(ngrams(palavras_sem_stopwords, 2)))

freq_dist = nltk.FreqDist(bigrams)
prob_dist = nltk.MLEProbDist(freq_dist)
number_of_bigrams = freq_dist.N()

    palavras_sem_stopwords = [palavra for palavra in sequence if palavra not in stopwords]
